 Main memory is central to the operation of a modern computer system .is a
repository of quickly accessible data shared by the CPU and I/O devices.
 Instructions must be in memory for the CPU to execute them.
 For a program to be executed, it must be mapped to absolute addresses and loaded
into memory. As the program executes, it accesses program instructions and data
from memory by generating these absolute addresses. After program termination, its 
memory space is declared available, and the next program can be loaded and
execute